---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import ProductMedia from '../components/ProductMedia.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Git worktree management for macOS — FlowTree" description="Create, import, organise, and work across Git worktrees without losing the state of your other branches.">
  <Navbar />
  <main>
    <PageHero eyebrow="Worktree management" title="A separate workspace for every stream of work." description="FlowTree makes Git worktrees the centre of your day: each one can keep its own branch, files, terminal sessions, status, and review flow ready when you return.">
      <div class="button-row"><a class="button button-primary" href="#workflow">See the workflow ↓</a><a class="button button-secondary" href={`${base}features/`}>All features</a></div>
    </PageHero>

    <section class="section-tight">
      <div class="container">
        <ProductMedia kind="image" src="images/flowtree-hero.png" alt="The FlowTree dashboard showing the main LifeSync project and worktrees grouped into In Progress, Planning, Archived, and Pull Request Review states." ratio="app" width={1444} height={925} />
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-border">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading center"><p class="eyebrow">Use your own mental model</p><h2>Organise by workstream or by task.</h2><p>FlowTree does not force one naming convention or project process.</p></div>
        <div class="card-grid two">
          <article class="card"><div class="feature-icon">∞</div><h3>Durable workstreams</h3><p>Create long-lived spaces such as Main Work, PR Reviews, Feature One, and Experiments. Change the branch inside a worktree as that stream moves forward.</p></article>
          <article class="card"><div class="feature-icon mint">✓</div><h3>Task-shaped worktrees</h3><p>Create focused spaces such as Implement Login Screen, Review Daniel’s Pull Request, or Fix Checkout Crash. Remove them when the task is complete.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="workflow" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading"><p class="eyebrow">A complete flow</p><h2>From new branch to finished change.</h2><p>FlowTree keeps the important transitions explicit while Git remains recognisable underneath.</p></div>
        <div class="workflow-grid">
          <article class="workflow-step"><h3>Create or import</h3><p>Start a new branch, use a local or remote branch, or bring an existing worktree under management.</p></article>
          <article class="workflow-step"><h3>Work in context</h3><p>Open terminal tabs or an IDE in the worktree’s directory, without touching the files in your other workspaces.</p></article>
          <article class="workflow-step"><h3>Review and ship</h3><p>Inspect changes, stage, commit, push, merge, or rebase, then archive or remove the worktree safely.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-border">
      <div class="narrow">
        <div class="split-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Useful from the first command</p><h2>New worktrees start as workable copies.</h2><p class="lede">Tracked files come from Git. FlowTree also carries forward usable untracked files from the main project while excluding ignored files and common generated directories such as build output, dependency folders, and IDE caches.</p><ul class="check-list"><li>Live creation progress across branch, worktree, and copy steps.</li><li>Automatic upstream setup when a matching remote branch exists.</li><li>Safe rollback when creation cannot complete.</li><li>Import and prune support for worktrees managed outside the app.</li></ul></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="narrow">
        <div class="split-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Stay oriented</p><h2>States turn a list of folders into a workflow.</h2><p class="lede">Create, rename, colour, reorder, and collapse the states that fit your process. Pin critical worktrees above their groups and see their latest Git status without opening each one.</p><ul class="check-list"><li>Editable states with names, icons, and colours.</li><li>Built-in starting points such as Planning, In Progress, Blocked, and PR Open.</li><li>Per-worktree pinning and renaming.</li><li>Multiple repositories in the same FlowTree window.</li></ul></div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <CTA title="Let your branches stay open for business." />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
